<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
    <title>Temple Map | Aahavaniya</title>

    <!-- Fonts & Styles -->
    <link
      href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Anek+Gurmukhi:wght@100..800&display=swap"
      rel="stylesheet"
    />
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/general.css" />
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/map.css" />
  </head>

  <body>
    <%- include('partials/header') %>

    <main class="map-page">
      <section class="map-page-header">
        <h1 class="map-title">Temple Map of India</h1>
        <div class="map-subtitle">
          <div class="map-subtitle-desktop">
            <p>
              The map highlights temples that shaped India's spiritual heritage.
              These ancient structures are not just places of worship, but
              living testaments to the artistic, cultural, and architectural
              brilliance of past civilizations.
            </p>
            <p>
              Use this map to explore their stories, locate them geographically,
              and better understand the spiritual geography of India.
            </p>
          </div>
          <p class="map-subtitle-mobile">
            Explore India's sacred legacy through temple markers — a map of
            devotion, art, and history.
          </p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <div class="svg-map-container">
        <svg
          width="801"
          height="910"
          viewBox="0 0 801 910"
          fill="none"
          xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
        >
          <%- include('partials/india-map') %>

          <!-- TEMPLE MARKERS -->
          <% temples.forEach(temple => { %>
          <g
            class="temple-marker"
            transform="translate(<%= temple.x %>, <%= temple.y %>)"
            data-name="<%= temple.name %>"
            data-dynasty="<%= temple.dynasty %>"
            data-age="<%= temple.age %>"
            data-style="<%= temple.style %>"
            data-location="<%= temple.location %>"
          >
            <circle r="4.5" fill="#e63946" />
          </g>

          <% }) %>
        </svg>
        <div id="temple-info-card" class="hidden">
          <h3 id="temple-name"></h3>
          <p><strong>Dynasty:</strong> <span id="temple-dynasty"></span></p>
          <p><strong>Period:</strong> <span id="temple-age"></span></p>
          <p><strong>Architecture:</strong> <span id="temple-style"></span></p>
          <p><strong>Location:</strong> <span id="temple-location"></span></p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="map-subtitle margin-top">
        <p>
          Every dot on this map marks more than a location — it marks a legacy.
          As you explore, consider how these temples once echoed with rituals,
          stories, and communities that shaped the soul of India.
        </p>
        <p>
          One of the aims of Project Aahavaniya is to spark curiosity for
          ancient temples and inspire people to visit and connect with their
          heritage.
        </p>
      </div>
    </main>

    <%- include('partials/footer') %>
    <script src="/js/temple-map.js"></script>
  </body>
</html>
